es to be—figured, and to consider what they seek to accomplish within their own scholarly practices. Together, the authors argue that a stronger critical self-awareness, an enhanced sense of the intellectual history of the methods of classics, and a greater understanding of the ethical and political implications of the decisions that the discipline makes will lead to a more engaged intellectual life, both for classicists and, ultimately, for society. A timely intervention into the present and future of the discipline, Postclassicisms will be required reading for professional classicists and students alike and a model for collaborative disciplinary intervention by scholars in other fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aClassical philologyxPhilosophy. 0aCritical theory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aclassicism.  aclassics.  acollaboration.  aconcept.  apostclassicism.  aresponsibility.  atime.  avalue.1 aBlanshard, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlenn, Glenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldhill, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGüthenke, Constanze, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Brooke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeonard, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorter, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVasunia, Phiroze, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhitmarsh, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter